## Boot test regression — node BLE pairing fails with btleplug/WinRT

Same root cause as PR #441 (modem), now fixed for the node.

### Bug

The node configures LESC Just Works security but never triggers pairing — no `ble_gap_security_initiate()` call in `on_connect`. Clients that don't initiate pairing (btleplug on WinRT) connect without authentication, and all GATT writes are rejected with `not yet authenticated`.

### Fixes

1. Server-initiated LESC pairing: Call `ble_gap_security_initiate(conn_handle)` in `on_connect` (ND-0904 criterion 3).
2. Pre-auth write buffering: Buffer GATT writes that arrive before LESC completes instead of rejecting them. Main loop only processes `pending_write` once `authenticated` is true (ND-0904 criterion 4).

### Spec updates (spec-first)

- ND-0904: Added criteria 3 (server-initiated pairing) and 4 (pre-auth write buffering)
- node-design.md: Document `ble_gap_security_initiate`, write buffering, updated event flow
- node-validation.md: Added T-N903a (passive client pairing) and T-N903b (pre-auth write buffered)

